# Supabase Database Schema

Schema files live in `supabase/`:

- `supabase/reset.sql` – selective wipe script (run first when resetting experiment data; preserves user tables)
- `supabase/schema.sql` – table/view definitions (run first)
- `supabase/rls_policies.sql` – Row Level Security policies (run second)
- `supabase/migrations/` – ordered SQL migrations applied by Supabase CLI / hosted projects

**Migrations filenames:** Always-applied `.cursor/rules/supabase-migrations.mdc` — prefix = real creation `YYYYMMDDHHMMSS` (user-stated date/time or `date +%Y%m%d%H%M%S`); never invented future dates.

The daily cron job is at `src/app/api/cron/daily/route.ts` (runs every weekday; AI ratings + portfolio only execute on rebalance day, prices saved daily). When `CRON_ERROR_EMAIL` is set it emails a digest every run: price-only days get a short digest (NASDAQ list source, `nasdaq_100_daily_raw` row count, last-sale price coverage); rebalance days include the full rating/portfolio section. Recorded issues and fatals appear in the same email.
The AI prompt template and JSON schema are at `src/lib/aiPrompt.ts`.

## Versioning

All strategy identity/version configuration derives from two files:
- `src/lib/ai-strategy-registry.ts` — master registry of all AIT strategy entries (aitCode, robotName, slug, appVersion, prompt, model, universe, defaultPortfolio).
- `src/lib/strategyConfig.ts` — derives `STRATEGY_CONFIG` and `APP_VERSION` from the active registry entry (`ACTIVE_STRATEGY_ENTRY`).

Single strategy lineage axis:

- `APP_VERSION` (semver, e.g. `v1.0.1`) — sole lineage axis. Bump for all changes: prompt text, model, portfolio rules, universe, ranking, etc.
- `STRATEGY_CONFIG` re-exports from the registry: canonical slug (`ait-1-daneel`), display name, aitCode, robotName, prompt, model, and defaultPortfolio tracking params.
- `GIT_COMMIT_SHA` captures the deploy commit (from `VERCEL_GIT_COMMIT_SHA`) stored in `ai_run_batches.git_commit_sha`.
- **Cron mismatch guard** (structural params only): throws if `index_name`, `rebalance_frequency`, `portfolio_size`, `weighting_method`, or `transaction_cost_bps` differ for the existing slug. Non-structural changes (`version`, `prompt_id`, `model_id`, `name`, `description`) are updated in-place.
- `MODEL_VERSION` is **removed**. All changes (prompt, model, portfolio rules) use `APP_VERSION`.

**Important**: When modifying `src/lib/aiPrompt.ts` or the AI model/prompt settings, bump `appVersion` in the active registry entry in `src/lib/ai-strategy-registry.ts` (which automatically bumps `APP_VERSION`). To create a new strategy lineage, add a new entry to `AI_STRATEGIES` with a new `aitCode` and `slug`.

Important: if you suggest changes to supabase/schema.sql, you must also suggest an SQL editor function to implement those changes in supabase.

You must also keep this file up to date.

## Two-layer Architecture

- **Layer A (AI rating model)**: `strategy_models` defines the AI strategy (prompt, model, universe, tracking portfolio). This is the rating engine.
- **Layer B (portfolios)**: `portfolio_configs` defines how a portfolio is built from the ratings (risk level, rebalance frequency, weighting, top_n). Users configure this layer independently.

## Tables (6 layers)

**Reference data**: `stocks` (includes `is_premium_stock` and **`is_guest_visible`** — subset of non-premium names for signed-out marketing surfaces; must satisfy `not is_guest_visible or not is_premium_stock`), `ai_prompts`, `ai_models`.

**NASDAQ-100 membership**: `nasdaq100_snapshots`, `nasdaq100_snapshot_stocks`, `nasdaq_100_daily_raw`.

**Strategy/version control (Layer A)**: `strategy_models` (canonical slug + AIT identity fields `ait_code` + `robot_name`; structural params define the rating engine; no `unique(name, version)` — slug is the sole identity; **`minimum_plan_tier`** `supporter` | `outperformer` = minimum subscription required for that strategy’s premium-scoped data such as per-stock `ai_analysis_runs` history — default **`outperformer`** for new rows; the default model (`is_default`) should be **`supporter`** so Supporter plans stay on one model only), `ai_run_batches`, `ai_analysis_runs`.

**Model-layer performance + research**: `strategy_portfolio_holdings`, `strategy_rebalance_actions`, `strategy_performance_weekly`, `strategy_quintile_returns`, `strategy_cross_sectional_regressions`. **RLS**: `strategy_performance_weekly`, quintile/regression tables remain publicly readable for marketing performance pages; `strategy_portfolio_holdings`, `strategy_rebalance_actions`, and `ai_analysis_runs` have **no** `anon`/`authenticated` SELECT (reads go through server routes using the service role after plan checks).

**Portfolio configs (Layer B)**: `portfolio_configs` (risk 1-5 × 4 freq × 2 weighting + risk 6 × 4 freq × equal only = 44 configs; risk 6 has top_n=1 so cap/equal are identical, only equal kept). Display names: `label` = `Top {n} · Weekly|Monthly|Quarterly|Yearly · Equal|Cap`; `risk_label` = tier badge (Conservative, Balanced, …). Canonical formatter: `src/lib/portfolio-config-display.ts` + migrations `20260320140000_portfolio_config_display_labels.sql`, `20260326100000_portfolio_config_label_frequency_then_weight.sql`. `strategy_portfolio_config_performance` (config-scoped performance rows keyed by strategy_id + config_id + run_date; includes `strategy_status` (in_progress/active), `compute_status` (pending/ready/failed), `next_rebalance_date`), `portfolio_config_compute_queue` (compute queue; service role only).

**User portfolio tables**: `user_portfolio_profiles` (active profiles per user; stores `config_id`, `investment_size`, `user_start_date`, `notifications_enabled`, `is_starting_portfolio` — set on onboarding follow for the “Starting portfolio” badge — separate from model-level performance), `user_overview_slot_assignments` (`user_id`, `slot_number` ≥ 1, `profile_id`; unique `(user_id, slot_number)` — platform overview grid; the same `profile_id` may appear in multiple slots), `user_portfolio_positions` (holdings snapshot per profile), plus existing `user_portfolio_stocks` (watchlist/saved holdings).

**Frontend-facing**: `nasdaq100_recommendations_current` (service role / cron only for full rows), **`nasdaq100_recommendations_current_public`** (service role only: same columns except **`latent_rank`**; no anon/authenticated SELECT), views `nasdaq100_scores_7d_view`, `nasdaq100_current_members`, `nasdaq100_latest_snapshot`.

**User account tables**: `user_profiles` (includes `portfolio_onboarding_done` boolean default false — portfolio wizard completion, RLS-updatable by owner; `auth_signup_provider` `email` \| `google` set only on insert from `auth.users` trigger (`raw_app_meta_data` → `provider`); `last_sign_in_at`, `last_sign_in_device_class` (`mobile` \| `desktop` \| `tablet` \| `unknown`), `last_sign_in_client` jsonb, `sign_in_count_mobile` / `sign_in_count_desktop` / `sign_in_count_tablet` / `sign_in_count_unknown` (non-negative; incremented atomically with last sign-in via RPC `record_user_sign_in_context`, called from `POST /api/auth/record-sign-in-context`); index `idx_user_profiles_email_lower` for signup duplicate check; Stripe snapshot `stripe_customer_id`, `stripe_subscription_id`, `stripe_current_period_end`, `stripe_cancel_at_period_end`, `stripe_pending_tier`, `stripe_pending_recurring_interval` (`month` \| `year`, null unless a same-tier cadence change is scheduled), `stripe_recurring_interval` (`month` \| `year`), `stripe_recurring_unit_amount` / `stripe_recurring_currency` (primary item recurring price) plus existing `subscription_tier` / event idempotency fields — **billing columns are not client-updatable**; trigger `user_profiles_protect_billing_columns` allows only `service_role` / privileged sessions to change them), `newsletter_subscribers` (`user_id -> auth.users(id)` now uses **`on delete cascade`** so deleting an auth user also removes the linked newsletter row).

## Key conventions

- All PKs are UUID (`gen_random_uuid()`).
- The cron job uses `createAdminClient()` (service role key), bypassing RLS.
- Frontend reads use anon/authenticated key with RLS policies.
- Cron precomputes ALL 48 configs via fan-out orchestrator (`/api/internal/compute-portfolio-configs-batch` → parallel `/api/internal/compute-portfolio-config` workers). Quarterly/yearly configs track weekly equity in buy-and-hold between rebalances. Manual backfill: `npm run backfill-configs`.
- **Model performance vs. user performance are always separate**: `strategy_performance_weekly` and `strategy_portfolio_config_performance` track the strategy since inception; `user_portfolio_profiles.user_start_date` tracks the user's entry point.
- When modifying the schema, update `supabase/schema.sql`, `supabase/rls_policies.sql`, the cron job, and this rule file.
- When modifying strategy parameters, prompt, model, or portfolio rules, bump `appVersion` in the active `AI_STRATEGIES` entry in `src/lib/ai-strategy-registry.ts`.
- SQL helper functions: `public.backfill_portfolio_config_mappings()` (backfills default config performance from weekly data), `public.verify_strategy_model_migration()` (validates FK integrity and slug uniqueness), `public.stock_ai_analysis_history_for_strategies(p_stock_id, p_strategy_ids, p_limit)` (latest analysis rows for a stock joined to batches; **service_role execute only** — API resolves `p_strategy_ids` from `strategy_models.minimum_plan_tier` + user tier).
